{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"About","page":{"layout":"document","title":"CUPTI Extensions","description":"The GitHub repo and complete tutorial is available at <https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/cupti-tutorial.","descriptionIsExcerpt":true,"bodyHtml":"<blockquote>\n<p>The GitHub repo and complete tutorial is available at <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/cupti-tutorial\">https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/cupti-tutorial</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This directory contains additional utilities and extensions for the CUPTI samples.</p>\n<h2 id=\"overview\">Overview</h2>\n<p>The extensions provide helper functions and utilities that simplify working with CUPTI APIs, particularly for more complex tasks like metric collection, evaluation, and result processing.</p>\n<h2 id=\"directory-structure\">Directory Structure</h2>\n<p>The extensions are organized into two main areas:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>include</strong>: Header files that define interfaces and utilities</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>c_util</strong>: Basic C utility functions (file operations, scope management, etc.)</li>\n<li><strong>profilerhost_util</strong>: Utilities for working with the CUPTI Profiler API</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>src</strong>: Implementation of the utilities</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>profilerhost_util</strong>: Source code for the profiler host utilities</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"key-components\">Key Components</h2>\n<h3 id=\"profiler-host-utilities\">Profiler Host Utilities</h3>\n<p>The profilerhost_util library provides functions for:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Metric Management</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Listing available metrics</li>\n<li>Getting metric descriptions and properties</li>\n<li>Converting between different metric formats</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Evaluation</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Processing counter data</li>\n<li>Calculating metric values from raw counter data</li>\n<li>Interpreting profiling results</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>File Operations</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Reading/writing metric data</li>\n<li>Managing profiling configurations</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"compatibility-notes\">Compatibility Notes</h2>\n<p>These extensions are designed to work with specific CUDA and CUPTI versions. Compatibility issues may arise when using with different versions of CUDA.</p>\n<p>If you encounter build errors when building the profilerhost_util library:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Check your CUDA version compatibility</li>\n<li>Use the dummy library created by the install.sh script for basic functionality</li>\n<li>For full functionality, you may need to update the code to match your CUDA/CUPTI version</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"usage\">Usage</h2>\n<p>Samples that require these extensions include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>autorange_profiling</li>\n<li>userrange_profiling</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These samples demonstrate more advanced CUPTI functionality that relies on the helper utilities provided in this directory.</p>\n<h2 id=\"building\">Building</h2>\n<p>The extensions are built automatically by the install.sh script in the main directory. However, if you need to build them manually:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">cd</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> src/profilerhost_util</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">make</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">cp</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> libprofilerHostUtil.</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">*</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ../../../lib64/</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"see-also\">See Also</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cupti/modules.html#group__CUPTI__PROFILER__API\">CUPTI Profiler API Documentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.nvidia.com/cupti/Cupti/modules.html#group__NVPERF__API\">NVPERF API Documentation</a></li>\n</ul>","headings":[{"id":"overview","text":"Overview","depth":2},{"id":"directory-structure","text":"Directory Structure","depth":2},{"id":"key-components","text":"Key Components","depth":2},{"id":"profiler-host-utilities","text":"Profiler Host Utilities","depth":3},{"id":"compatibility-notes","text":"Compatibility Notes","depth":2},{"id":"usage","text":"Usage","depth":2},{"id":"building","text":"Building","depth":2},{"id":"see-also","text":"See Also","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/others/cupti-tutorial/extensions/README.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2025-06-17T09:26:20.000Z","createdAt":"2025-06-17T09:19:24.000Z","authors":[{"name":"github-actions[bot]","email":"41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com"}]},"path":"/others/cupti-tutorial/extensions/","alternates":{"en":"/others/cupti-tutorial/extensions/","zh":"/zh/others/cupti-tutorial/extensions/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"About Eunomia","description":"The broader Eunomia project family, including GPU tutorials, research notes, experiments, and related open-source tools.","href":"/others/"},"previous":{"title":"CUPTI Event Sampling Tutorial","description":"The GitHub repo and complete tutorial is available at <https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/cupti-tutorial.","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/event_sampling/"},"next":{"title":"CUPTI Nested Range Profiling Tutorial","description":"The GitHub repo and complete tutorial is available at <https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/cupti-tutorial.","href":"/others/cupti-tutorial/nested_range_profiling/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"About Eunomia","items":[{"title":"About Eunomia","href":"/others/","depth":0},{"title":"BPF-Benchmark","href":"/others/bpf-benchmark/","depth":1},{"title":"bpf-compatible","href":"/others/bpf-compatible/","depth":1},{"title":"Contributing to eunomia-bpf","href":"/others/contribute/","depth":1},{"title":"Tutori